verbose_text: An Atypical Caustic Ingestion--Zinc Chloride with Hyperzincemia Robert C Pueringer, Jon B Cole, Annie M Arens Minnesota Poison Control Center, Minneapolis, MN, USA Background : Zinc chloride ingestions are infrequent and typically lead to corrosive gastrointestinal injury and rarely lethargy or shock.
evidence: Zinc chloride ingestions are infrequent and typically lead to corrosive gastrointestinal injury
